@prefix retrofit: <https://ggen.dev/ontology/retrofit#> .
@prefix rdf:      <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:     <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:      <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# Load-path facts for ggen's 6 real load paths, as-found 2026-07-20.
# Grounded in: docs/retrofit/ggen/as-found/{repository,generation-system,
# architecture-semantics}.md, this-pass gh api checks (branch protection 404,
# single collaborator), and .github/workflows/release.yml inspection.
# retrofit:standing values: "Blocking" | "Accepted" | "Unknown" — never silently
# filled; see retrofit:evidence / retrofit:evidencePath on each individual.

retrofit:LoadPath a rdfs:Class .
retrofit:SPOF a rdfs:Class .

retrofit:standing a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:comment "Blocking | Accepted | Unknown" .
retrofit:evidence a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:comment "Free-text pointer to the as-found evidence backing this fact." .
retrofit:evidencePath a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:comment "Repo-relative path to the evidence artifact." .
retrofit:affects a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:domain retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:range retrofit:LoadPath .

## ---------------------------------------------------------------- Load paths

retrofit:GenerationPath a retrofit:LoadPath ;
    rdfs:label "Generation" ;
    retrofit:entryPoint "crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs" ;
    retrofit:evidencePath "docs/retrofit/ggen/as-found/generation-system.md" .

retrofit:SelfGenerationPath a retrofit:LoadPath ;
    rdfs:label "Self-generation" ;
    retrofit:entryPoint ".ggen-v2/receipt.json" ;
    retrofit:evidencePath "docs/retrofit/ggen/as-found/generation-system.md" .

retrofit:PullRequestPath a retrofit:LoadPath ;
    rdfs:label "Pull-request" ;
    retrofit:entryPoint ".github/workflows/ci.yml" ;
    retrofit:evidence "gh api repos/seanchatmangpt/ggen/branches/main/protection -> 404" .

retrofit:ReleasePath a retrofit:LoadPath ;
    rdfs:label "Release" ;
    retrofit:entryPoint ".github/workflows/release.yml" ;
    retrofit:evidence "release.yml: on: push: tags: + workflow_dispatch, confirmed by direct read" .

retrofit:ConstitutionPath a retrofit:LoadPath ;
    rdfs:label "Constitution" ;
    retrofit:entryPoint "packs/ggen-constitution-pack/ontology.ttl" ;
    retrofit:evidencePath "docs/retrofit/ggen/as-found/architecture-semantics.md" .

retrofit:FleetManagementPath a retrofit:LoadPath ;
    rdfs:label "Fleet-management" ;
    retrofit:entryPoint "scripts/gh/fleet-census.sh" ;
    retrofit:evidencePath "docs/gh-terraform/FLEET-CENSUS.md" .

## ---------------------------------------------------------------- SPOFs

retrofit:SchemaDispatchAmbiguity a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "ggen.toml two-schema dispatch -- RESOLVED, stale citation" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:GenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "STALE CITATION, real guard already exists: sync.rs Stage 0 (line 170) no longer calls the old ad-hoc generation_rules::has_generation_rules pre-parse this SPOF cited -- it calls crate::schema_dispatch::load(root), a dedicated module (specs/014-ggen-core-replacement, correction 2 / Blocker A part 2) that is the SINGLE shared dispatch point for all 6 former ad-hoc call sites, backed by ggen_config::classify_ggen_toml's real Ambiguous{matched} classification (typed error FM-CONFIG-101) when more than one schema's markers fire simultaneously. 14/14 config_schema tests pass, including document_with_conflicting_markers_is_ambiguous and ambiguous_document_reports_the_ambiguous_code. This SPOF predates that fix's ledger update -- resolved by prior work (BUG-005 in that ticket's history), not by this generation; restanding only." .

retrofit:GeneratedTableDriftManifested a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "Generated architecture.md pack-inventory table -- RESOLVED, guard added" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:GenerationPath, retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "REPAIRED 2026-07-21: found drifted a THIRD time (32-vs-39, worse than the 28-vs-32/32-vs-33 this SPOF originally cited) -- confirming a one-time number bump never fixes recurring drift. Root cause: rf:packCount in .specify/repo-facts.ttl was a hand-maintained literal with nothing ever re-checking it. Real fix: scripts/ci/guard-pack-count.sh (new, matches the established guard-*.sh house pattern) compares rf:packCount against a live `find packs -mindepth 1 -maxdepth 1 -type d` count and refuses (BUILD_BROKEN) on any mismatch; wired into justfile's pre-commit chain as guard-pack-count. Sabotage-proven: tampering rf:packCount to a wrong value produces the exact refusal naming both counts; restoring it passes. rf:packCount corrected 32->39 (the real current count) as part of this fix." .

retrofit:FreezeAlwaysNoDriftDetection a retrofit:SPOF ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_21 "RESOLVED, both halves, retrofit/ggen-self-g2 commits c0cddb253+69729d219 (ctl:O-5-restand-FreezeAlwaysNoDriftDetection, CLOSED in ../controller/obligations.ttl -- this entry was stale relative to that closure until this bookkeeping pass). write.rs's check_freeze now takes rendered_body and, for FreezePolicy::Always, compares it against on-disk content: identical content skips with an explicit no-drift reason, differing content skips with a DRIFT-marked reason -- mutation behavior is unchanged (still skips either way, preserving hand-completed-bootstrap semantics per CLAUDE.md's mode=Create precedent), only the previously-silent case now produces a distinguishable signal. sync.rs's admission-item construction detects the DRIFT marker and produces Fail+Quarantined with obligations_created:[FROZEN-DRIFT:<path>], pulling derived Andon off Green instead of silently reporting Skipped as if nothing happened. Verified: 7 write.rs unit tests (freeze_always_{absent_target_writes_normally,identical_content_skips_with_no_drift_reason,drifted_content_skips_but_reports_drift,hand_completed_bootstrap_file_reports_real_drift,second_sync_idempotent_when_no_drift}) plus 2 frontmatter_fields_e2e tests parsing a real receipt.json (freeze_always_drift_is_quarantined_and_creates_an_obligation_in_the_real_receipt, freeze_always_no_drift_stays_admitted_with_no_obligation), including a no-drift control proving the detection discriminates rather than always-flagging." ;
    rdfs:label "write.rs freeze policy 'always' skips unconditionally with no drift check" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:GenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidencePath "crates/ggen-engine/src/write.rs" .

retrofit:ReflexiveReceiptSkip a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "Sanctioned silent-skip of malformed reflexive-receipt log line" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:GenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "CONFIRMED via direct code read, crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs ~L312-355: only active when [law].reflexive=true (opt-in, off by default -- bounded blast radius). A malformed receipt-log.jsonl line is NOT silently dropped: its own comment names this as the one deliberate exception to fail-closed elsewhere in the pipeline (the log is external history not byte-controlled by this sync's author -- an older-tool-version or hand-edited line must not brick every future sync), and the skip IS recorded, not hidden: closure.insert(\"receipt-log:MALFORMED-N\", \"MALFORMED\") makes it visible in the receipt's own closure map. Accepted standing is correct: reasoned, disclosed, auditable exception, not an undisclosed defect." .

retrofit:EquivalenceMapNotLive a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "7 of 8 receipt equivalence classes live and Equivalent; compiled_binary Unknown by deliberate, evidence-backed design" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "Updated 2026-07-21 (self-retrofit Generation 2, PR #360): the `evidence` class is now live -- ggen-verify-pack's gates 010/020 were wired into ggen's own [validation].gates (previously only [ontology].imports admitted its facts, never routing through crate::pack::resolve() which evaluates gates), and proven causal both directions: a real clippy fix flipped a recorded ver:exitCode row from red to green and the live sync's refusal-citation count dropped accordingly; a real adversarial tamper of a currently-green fact flipped a row red, cited by name. source/config remain Divergent; compiled_binary/docs/tests/receipts/gates remain Unknown -- narrowing what's still open, not the whole original claim. ggen-verify-pack's own gates 030/040/050 (freshness/andon-regression/output-count-regression) remain unwired by design: this repo's own ggen.toml is the declarative-rules schema, which has no [law].reflexive, so those three gates could never fire here." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22a "CORRECTION + real progress. The 2026-07-21 update above conflated two distinct mechanisms and its 'evidence class now live' claim was wrong: gates 010/020 gate on ver:Check/ver:RequiredCheck facts (validation refusal), a different mechanism from the `evidence` EQUIVALENCE class, which requires ver:EvidenceCheck facts from a separate, still-unwired producer (produce_evidence_check_sh.tmpl) -- confirmed by reading the live receipt (`.ggen-v2/receipt.json`'s `record.v2.equivalence`) directly rather than re-deriving the prose: `evidence` is still Unknown today. What the 2026-07-21 pass actually achieved (undocumented until now): `tests` and `gates` were already Equivalent, piggybacking on ver:Check facts already imported via evidence/ontology.ttl -- a real but different win than what was claimed. This pass closes `docs` for real: packs/ggen-verify-pack/ontology.ttl already declared a complete ver:Producer \"docs\" config (ver:docsDir) and packs/ggen-verify-pack/templates/produce_docs_manifest_sh.tmpl already existed, fully self-contained -- this repo's declarative-rules ggen.toml just never wired an equivalent generation rule (the same schema gap verify-evidence-emitter/-report already solved for a different producer). Added .specify/templates/verify/produce_docs_manifest_sh.sh.tera (declarative-rules mirror, same convention as verify_evidence_sh.sh.tera), one [[generation.rules]] entry ('verify-docs-manifest-producer'), ran the emitted scripts/produce-docs-manifest.sh (real execution: 1236 real sha256 hashes over docs/, evidence/producers/docs-manifest.ttl), added that path to [ontology].imports, then ran `ggen sync run` twice (first run has no prior admitted docs-manifest facts to compare against, so `docs` reads Unknown; second run's `record.v2.equivalence.docs` reads `Equivalent`, real receipt output, not inferred). `ggen receipt verify` after both runs: valid:true, signed:true, signature_valid:true -- chain integrity unbroken. Real current state: source/config/tests/gates/docs all Equivalent; compiled_binary/receipts/evidence remain Unknown (3, not 5). compiled_binary is documented EXPENSIVE-by-design (double cold build, has its own --skip marker) -- closing it is a real but different-shaped cost/benefit question, not a wiring gap like docs was. receipts and evidence each have their own already-scaffolded ver:Producer configs and templates (produce_receipts_check_sh.tmpl, produce_evidence_check_sh.tmpl) not yet wired -- same shape of work as this pass, each independently actionable as its own next step. Standing correctly remains Blocking (3 real gaps, not fully closed), but the false 'evidence is live' claim is now corrected and one real class is closed with receipt-verified evidence." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22b "Real progress, same shape as the docs pass. Closes `receipts` for real: packs/ggen-verify-pack's ver:Producer \"receipts\" config and produce_receipts_check_sh.tmpl (schema-validates + hash-chain-replays .ggen-v2/receipt-log.jsonl) were already complete; added the same declarative-rules mirror pattern (.specify/templates/verify/produce_receipts_check_sh.sh.tera, one [[generation.rules]] entry, evidence/producers/receipts-check.ttl in [ontology].imports). REAL BUG FOUND AND FIXED in the mirror (not in the pack itself, which may correctly serve other consumers with a different receipt shape): the pack's own template checks each receipt-log record for a `schema` field; ggen's real records (crates/praxis-core/src/receipt_record.rs) have no such field -- the actual per-record version marker is `version` (confirmed: every one of 97 real records carries `\"version\": 1`). Checking the pack's literal `schema` key against ggen's real data would report exitCode 1 (missing field) unconditionally, an honest-looking but false negative -- this mirror checks `version` instead, evidence-based, not guessed. Verified by real execution: ran the emitted scripts/produce-receipts-check.sh (real python schema-validate + chain-replay over 97 records), got exit 0 with a genuine replayed chain head; `ggen sync run` admits it and `record.v2.equivalence.receipts` reads `Equivalent` on the FIRST run (unlike docs, which needed two runs) -- confirms the comparison is real chain-continuity verification (replayed head matches the previous receipt's own recorded head), not static content identity. `ggen receipt verify` after every run in this pass: valid/signed/signature_valid all true throughout. OPERATIONAL CAVEAT, disclosed not hidden: because `ggen sync run` unconditionally appends a new receipt entry (advancing the chain head) every single time it runs, the receipts producer script must be re-run immediately before each sync a consumer wants to read as green -- a sync run without a fresh produce-receipts-check.sh beforehand will correctly show `receipts: Divergent` (observed directly during this pass: running sync twice in a row without re-running the producer between them correctly flagged the staleness, not a bug -- the mechanism catching exactly the kind of drift it exists to catch). CI/consumers wanting a green receipts class need this producer step wired before their sync invocation; this pass did not wire that into any CI job, since ci.yml doesn't currently run `ggen sync run` itself as a gate (out of scope for this pass -- a real follow-on if CI-time verification of this class is wanted). Also observed and left alone (expected, not a defect): `source` shows Divergent on every run in this pass, because evidence/producers/receipts-check.ttl's own content (it records the replayed head) inherently changes every time the producer is re-run -- an unavoidable consequence of tracking an ever-advancing hash chain as a closure input, not something to chase a false 'stable source' fix for. Real current state after this pass: source/config/tests/gates/docs/receipts all Equivalent; compiled_binary/evidence remain Unknown (2, not 3). compiled_binary stays EXPENSIVE-by-design (unchanged reasoning from the prior pass). evidence has its own already-scaffolded producer (produce_evidence_check_sh.tmpl) not yet wired -- same shape of work as docs/receipts, independently actionable as the next step. Standing correctly remains Blocking (2 real gaps left)." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22c "CLOSURE. Wires `evidence` for real, the last mechanically-closeable class: packs/ggen-verify-pack's ver:Producer \"evidence\" config (ver:freshnessWindowHours 168) and produce_evidence_check_sh.tmpl (completeness: every ver:RequiredCheck name present as a ver:Check in evidence/ontology.ttl; freshness: evidence commit age vs HEAD within the window) were already complete -- same declarative-rules mirror pattern as docs/receipts (.specify/templates/verify/produce_evidence_check_sh.sh.tera, one [[generation.rules]] entry, evidence/producers/evidence-check.ttl in [ontology].imports; this mirror needed two sparql() calls, `required` and `cfg`, since the pack's own frontmatter template used two named queries). Verified by real execution: ran the emitted scripts/produce-evidence-check.sh, exit 0 (\"ok\", genuine completeness+freshness pass over the real ver:RequiredCheck set); `ggen sync run` admits it and `record.v2.equivalence.evidence` reads `Equivalent`. `ggen receipt verify`: valid/signed/signature_valid all true. Real current state: source/config/tests/gates/docs/receipts/evidence all Equivalent -- 7 of 8 classes now live, verified, and correctly comparing recorded facts against reality on every sync. Only `compiled_binary` remains Unknown.\n\nRESTANDING TO ACCEPTED, with the evidentiary basis stated plainly so a future session can check it, not just trust it: `compiled_binary`'s absence is not an unaddressed risk in the sense this SPOF originally named (a self-generation path nobody has verified) -- the property it would check (does ggen's own compiled binary reproduce byte-identically build-over-build) is ALREADY independently verified, by a STRONGER mechanism than this equivalence class would even provide: retrofit:ReleaseGateBrokenForWeeks (restood Accepted, PR #434) proved genuine byte-identical reproducibility for ggen's real release build targets ACROSS INDEPENDENTLY-PROVISIONED HOSTS (release.yml run 29919854272, 8 Cross-Host Repro replicas + 4 Verify Cross-Host Reproducibility jobs, all real, all passed) -- a cross-host guarantee, strictly stronger than compiled_binary's same-host double-cold-build design. Combined with compiled_binary's own documented EXPENSIVE-by-design status (double cold build, explicit ver:skipped marker signaling it was designed to be optional, not routinely run), this is a genuine 'bounded accepted risk with evidence' terminal state, not a deferred judgment call: the underlying question this equivalence class exists to answer is already answered, by a citable, real, closed SPOF with real run evidence -- not by assumption. A future session wiring compiled_binary anyway (e.g. as a periodic, freshness-windowed check rather than every-sync) would be real, welcome, additive work, but its absence no longer represents unverified risk on retrofit:SelfGenerationPath. cargo check --workspace, fmt-check, test-lib (433/433) all clean for this pass's changes." .

retrofit:StandingCeilingHardcoded a retrofit:SPOF ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_21 "Mechanism designed and implemented (ctl:O-Promotion, CLOSED, commit 3f080f7fa, ../controller/obligations.ttl); production ceiling itself deliberately UNCHANGED, so Blocking stands correctly, but for a narrower reason than before. NOT a literal hardcoded constant -- praxis_core::receipt_epoch::compute_ceiling genuinely computes `recoverable(prev).min(supported(components))` each generation, and recoverable(prev)=prev is the identity function by explicit design (receipt_epoch.rs:173-176), so once any generation's ceiling reads LegacyObserved it can never exceed it via the normal meet path -- confirmed still live in the current receipt.json. The escape hatch now exists and is real, tested, and callable: PromotionWitness{from_ceiling,to_ceiling,evidence_receipts,closed_obligations,verifier_identity,authorization_basis} + validate_promotion() + ReceiptEpochV2Builder::with_verified_promotion(), 8 passing tests covering valid promotion, self-authored refusal, stale/non-raising/empty-field refusals, and no-regression on normal (non-witnessed) generations. Deliberately NOT wired into sync.rs's production builder chain (line 2453 still uses the unwitnessed path): who holds verifier_identity trust in ggen's own autonomous self-retrofit context -- i.e. who is authorized to vouch that ggen's own ceiling may rise -- is genuine external business intent, not derivable from repository law, and is the correct DESIGN_UNCERTAINTY_LAW escalation case. Remains Blocking honestly: the floor is still real and still unaddressed in production; what changed is that 'needs a real architecture decision' is no longer an open question -- the decision is made and implemented, only the trust-authority wiring is outstanding." ;
    rdfs:label "standing_ceiling hardcoded to LegacyObserved" ;
    retrofit:standing "Blocking" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidencePath ".ggen-v2/receipt.json" .

retrofit:AndonHardcodedGreen a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "andon field unconditionally hardcoded Green in write_receipt" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:SelfGenerationPath, retrofit:ConstitutionPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "RESOLVED as-found 2026-07-20/21 retrofit item #2 verification pass: sync.rs's legacy `andon` field (now ~L2464-2476, `write_receipt`) is derived from `epoch.andon: AndonLevel` via `derive_andon`/`ComponentLevels` precedence (crates/praxis-core/src/receipt_epoch.rs), not a hardcoded literal -- the surrounding comment at sync.rs:2461-2463 documents this as the exact migration that removed the hardcoded-Green literal this SPOF names (landed in one of #322/#336/#346, predating this retrofit item's assignment). A Stage 2b (validate) gate/denial refusal returns `Err` via `?` before `write_receipt` is ever called (sync.rs:482-559), so a red gate cannot reach the receipt as a false Green either -- confirmed live: `.ggen-v2/receipt.json`'s `record.andon` and `record.v2.andon` both read \"Green\" after a real `ggen sync run` on an unmodified tree, and `cargo build -p ggen-cli-lib --bin ggen` is clean. This as-found fact supersedes the stale evidencePath (`sync.rs:1857`, which is now inside a different fn, `verify_check_axis`, not `write_receipt`); no source change was required for this item." .

retrofit:DualObligationCounters a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "Legacy obligation_count=4 vs v2 Tracked{required:9,discharged:5} disagree by design" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "CONFIRMED via direct code read: the two counters are genuinely different mechanisms over different data, not a drifted duplicate of the same fact. Legacy record.obligation_count (crates/praxis-core/src/law.rs:320/414) = self.obligations.len(), a coarse count of the v1 LawObject's own Vec<Obligation>. v2's ObligationCount::Tracked{required,discharged} (crates/praxis-core/src/receipt_epoch.rs:420-435, compute_obligation_count) sums obligations_created/obligations_discharged across every itemized AdmissionItem -- a finer-grained, per-evidence-item accounting introduced with v2 that the legacy field was never redefined to match. Accepted standing is correct: they will keep disagreeing by construction (different layers, different granularity), and that's disclosed, not hidden." .

retrofit:SabotageFixtureCoverageGap a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "Sabotage fixture coverage -- ALL 13 named fixtures now tested (dogfood 8/8, ma 2/2, self-monitoring 3/3)" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdateG14 "FINAL LEG CLOSED, retrofit/ggen-self-g14: new crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/ma_case_adversarial_fixtures.rs (2 tests) and self_monitoring_lifecycle_fixtures.rs (3 tests), all through the real kh: mechanism or the pack's shipped query surface. mega-deal-second-request.ttl: BOTH obligations (hsr-act + second-request-review) derived for deal MHC-2026-0311 -- the committed replacement for the scratch-binary verification its header disclosed. target-org-colliding.ttl: fixture-integrity pinned (parses standalone + the staged Azure-IRI collision with acquirer-org.ttl is genuinely present via aztf subject-set intersection); detection coverage honestly scoped OUT -- f31_org_merge lives in the multifractal-workflow crate, not this repo. pattern-overdue.ttl: OverdueEscalationObligation + High/ActNow derived through the hook mechanism. pattern-ungoverned.ttl: exactly one UngovernedTransition (turn-1->turn-2), zero EscalationObligations. pattern-fires-discharged.ttl: shipped open_obligations.rq returns 0 rows; control = same node with status flipped to Open returns 1 (discriminates on status, all else byte-identical). TWO residual findings recorded, not papered over: (a) open_obligations.rq can NEVER match any hook-derived node -- the base derive hook constructs no status/severity/deadlineHint and the prioritized variants type nodes PrioritizedEscalationObligation, so the query's full required property set on `a smon:EscalationObligation` is only satisfiable by hand-authored nodes; which side is wrong is pack law needing its own decision. (b) STRSTARTS/STR in FILTER is ANOTHER silently-zero-rows construct on praxis-graphlaw's executor (probed live writing the collision test), joining the documented ORDER BY and now-refused VALUES gaps -- the silent-unsupported class is systematic, strengthening the case for an executor-level unsupported-construct audit. Accepted: every fixture this SPOF originally named now has committed, passing coverage." ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "DOGFOOD LEG REPAIRED, retrofit/ggen-self-g13: new crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/dogfood_lifecycle_hook_actuation.rs (10 tests, all passing) covers all 8 previously-zero-reference fixtures through the REAL kh: hook mechanism (load_hook_pack + materialize, the ma_case_hook_actuation.rs pattern): session-malformed (parse refusal), session-error-not-blocked (fire precision -- no obligation from dfl:Error, asserted on triple shape, not dump substrings, since hook kh:query literals contain the Obligation IRI as text), session-discharged (dischargedBy event-5 + Discharged status), session-adversarial-discharge (different-agent Ok does NOT discharge), session-cross-session-collision (same-agent different-session neither discharges nor escalates), session-escalated (escalatedBy event-7 AND dischargedBy event-5 coexisting by design), session-not-yet-overdue (2 later events -- no escalation, the >=3 boundary), and session-iri-collision -- the last against the pack's CURRENT law (shapes.ttl was deleted in the SHACL->SPARQL-gates migration, ad9106702; the maxCount law lives in gates/020_single_valued.rq now), running the real committed gate text on oxigraph (the engine production gates actually run on) with a session-good zero-rows control; an equivalent engine-level --shapes refusal test was added to lint_validate_e2e.rs. Writing this surfaced and repaired TWO further real defects, recorded as their own SPOF entries below: CiIntegrationTestsNeverRun (how lint_validate_e2e's shapes tests rotted silently) and GraphLawValuesSilentZeroRows (repaired fail-closed same cycle). REMAINING, still Blocking: ma-case-study-pack's target-org-colliding.ttl + mega-deal-second-request.ttl and self-monitoring-pack's pattern-overdue/pattern-ungoverned/pattern-fires-discharged.ttl -- 5 named fixtures, same bounded follow-on shape as the leg just closed." .

retrofit:CiIntegrationTestsNeverRun a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "CI's Test job runs `cargo test --lib` only -- every crate's tests/ directory is invisible to CI -- CLOSED" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:PullRequestPath, retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "DISCOVERED 2026-07-21 (retrofit/ggen-self-g13) with two independent concrete manifestations, not hypothetically: (1) lint_validate_e2e.rs's two SHACL --shapes tests referenced packs/dogfood-lifecycle-pack/shapes.ttl, DELETED in commit ad9106702's SHACL->SPARQL-gates migration -- both tests fail on a plain `cargo test -p ggen-engine --test lint_validate_e2e` yet every PR since merged with Test green, because .github/workflows/ci.yml's Test job (line ~137) runs `cargo test --workspace --lib --exclude ggen-lsp` -- integration tests never compile or run in CI (repaired this cycle: the tests now carry a self-contained shapes fixture and pass 10/10). (2) A full `cargo test -p praxis-graphlaw --no-fail-fast` shows 20 pre-existing failing integration tests across 8 suites (chatman_acceptance_agents 7, knowledge_hooks_e2e_tier4 4, and 6 more suites; predominantly a 'SPARQL parse error at 1:18' class) -- confirmed pre-existing via an A/B run against unmodified HEAD (byte-identical failing sets with and without this cycle's changes), all invisible to CI for the same reason. NOT fixed this cycle: turning integration tests on in CI is real workflow surgery (the 20 red tests must be fixed or explicitly quarantined FIRST, or the flip would redden every PR) -- named as its own follow-on obligation with the failing-suite inventory captured, not silently deferred." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_21b "PARTIAL CLOSURE, this cycle: (a) chatman_acceptance_agents' 7 failures fixed for real (commit 7892a40df, PR #373, merged) -- fixtures authored against the real schema, not the doc-cited nonexistent one. (b) A fresh `cargo test -p praxis-graphlaw --no-fail-fast` (2026-07-21, retrofit/ggen-self-g18) confirms the real, current, stable inventory is now exactly 10 failing tests, not 20: test_hook_alias_unknown_predicate_refused, test_hook_alias_vocabulary_identical_receipts, test_pattern4_canonical_edges_sorted, test_s4_automated_quarantine_and_refusal, test_s4_ledger_balance_enforcement_and_audit, test_s4_materialized_view_cache_maintenance, test_s4_state_machine_transition_control, test_sparql_ask_constraint, test_sparql_constraint_combined_with_ordinary_constraints, test_sparql_select_constraint -- none individually root-caused yet this pass. (c) The CI-visibility half of this SPOF is now closed: .github/workflows/ci.yml gained a new `integration-tests (advisory)` job running the full `cargo test --workspace --exclude ggen-lsp`, deliberately non-blocking (matches the existing `lsp-crates (advisory)` precedent, no continue-on-error masking) until the remaining 10 are fixed or quarantined. Standing correctly remains Blocking: the false-Green risk itself (integration tests silently never running, required checks passing regardless) is not resolved until this job is promoted to required, which needs the 10 above closed first." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22 "FULL CLOSURE (retrofit/ggen-self-g4): all 10 remaining failures individually root-caused and fixed for real -- 8 were test-authoring bugs, 2 were genuine product defects (both repaired with a pinned regression test, not just disclosed). TEST BUGS: (1) `test_s4_automated_quarantine_and_refusal`/`test_s4_materialized_view_cache_maintenance` (knowledge_hooks_e2e_tier4.rs) used a `CONSTRUCT { GRAPH <iri> { ... } } WHERE {...}` action query -- invalid per the SPARQL 1.1 spec itself (ConstructTemplate has no GRAPH clause option, W3C sparql11-query#rConstructTemplate), confirmed via a direct spargebra probe on the isolated query text; fixed by dropping the invalid GRAPH-quad template. (2) `test_s4_ledger_balance_enforcement_and_audit`/`test_s4_state_machine_transition_control` (same file) called `.unwrap()` on `materialize()` expecting `Ok(vec![])` when a `kh:effect \"refuse\"` hook fires; the established, already-tested contract (`reasoner/mod.rs:739`'s `return Err(...)`, matching `business_logic_cases[_suite1].rs::test_suite1_minimal_refusal_surfaces_reason`) is that refusal returns `Err`, not silent rollback-to-Ok -- fixed to assert `res.is_err()`. (3) `test_hook_alias_unknown_predicate_refused` (knowledge_hooks_e2e_tier5.rs) was a REAL product bug, not a test bug -- see below. (4) `test_hook_alias_vocabulary_identical_receipts` (same file) compared receipts from two hook packs using DIFFERENT subject IRIs (`ex:h_canonical` vs `ex:h_alias`); the hook IRI is embedded verbatim in every emitted delta-quad line (`hooks::construct::serialize_delta_quad`'s `hook_wrapped`), so different IRIs necessarily hash differently -- fixed by holding the subject IRI fixed across both variants, isolating the one real variable (namespace aliasing) the test exists to check. (5) `test_pattern4_canonical_edges_sorted` (pattern4_equivalence_canonicalization.rs) concatenated `[class_edges, property_edges, term_edges]` and asserted the concat was sorted -- each list is independently sorted by `UnionFind::render_canonical`, but concatenating three independently-sorted-but-mutually-unordered lists is not itself sorted (proven: with only owl:sameAs triples, `canonicalize_equivalences` populates identical edges into ALL THREE lists by design -- see `EquivalenceCanonical`'s own field docs -- so the naive concat is a sawtooth). The crate already has the correct combinator for this, `render_all_equivalences_canonical` (tested, but not previously re-exported from `shacl::mod.rs`) -- exported and the test switched to use it instead of reimplementing the same contract incorrectly ad hoc. (6)-(8) `test_sparql_ask_constraint`/`test_sparql_select_constraint` (shacl_validation.rs + byte-identical duplicates in shacl_validation_extended.rs) and `test_sparql_constraint_combined_with_ordinary_constraints` (shacl_sparql_stress.rs) all asserted `sh:sparql` constraints (sh:ask/sh:select) actively produce violations -- but `SHACL_SPARQL_BOUNDARY = \"CORE_ONLY\"` (model.rs, PROJ-407 Step 2, a deliberate v26.7.8 threat-model decision pinned by its own passing `shacl_test.rs` unit test) makes `check_sparql_boundary` skip evaluating every `sh:sparql` constraint node entirely (validate.rs:572) -- these tests were written assuming a different (SPARQL-enabled) policy than the one actually in force. Fixed to assert the real, current, deliberate contract (sh:sparql inert, only SHACL-Core constraints on the same shape still enforced) with an explanatory NOTE citing the boundary decision, rather than reversing that decision (a real production shapes file, ontologies/shapes/process-conformance.shacl.ttl, uses sh:sparql and has zero found Rust consumers to safely re-verify against within this pass's scope -- see the new ShaclSparqlBoundaryDocDrift SPOF entry below for the disclosed, deliberately-not-fixed-here doc/implementation gap this surfaced). PRODUCT DEFECTS (both repaired, not disclosed-only): (A) `test_hook_alias_unknown_predicate_refused` -- `rewrite_hook_alias` (hooks/parsing.rs) silently left any `hook:`-namespaced predicate NOT in `HOOK_ALIAS_MAP` unrewritten, so it stayed in the `hook:` namespace where EVERY downstream validation check (SHACL closed-shape, `ALLOWED_KH_PREDICATES`) only inspects `kh:`-prefixed predicates -- a fail-open gap contradicting the function's own doc comment ('will be rejected in validation if unsupported'). Fixed at the source: `rewrite_hook_alias` now returns `Err` for any unrecognized `hook:` alias predicate. (B) surfaced independently while fixing (1)/test 1 above: this engine's custom SPARQL executor (`sparql/plan.rs`'s `extract_query_plan`) has no `GraphPattern::Graph` arm and silently falls into `_ => PlanNode::Done` (`PlanNode::Done => Box::new(empty())` in sparql/mod.rs) for ANY `GRAPH <iri> { ... }` WHERE-clause pattern -- proven live via a direct probe (an ASK query with a GRAPH clause over a store containing a matching graph-scoped quad still returned zero rows / no hook fire). This is the SAME silent-zero-rows failure class already tracked and fixed for VALUES/ORDER BY/etc. (retrofit:GraphLawValuesSilentZeroRows) -- repaired the same way: `find_unsupported_construct` (lib.rs) now refuses GRAPH loudly instead of transparently recursing past it, joining that established fail-closed net; pinned as a new case in `tests/sparql_unsupported_refusal.rs`'s battery (both the refused-not-silent half and the not-over-blocking half). Full-suite evidence: `cargo test -p praxis-graphlaw --no-fail-fast` 0 failures (run twice, clean both times, plus an isolated re-run of the one target that hit a transient shared-disk linker ENOSPC in the parallel run -- confirmed a disk-contention artifact, not a code regression, by rerunning that target alone: 13/13 pass); `cargo check --workspace --exclude ggen-lsp` and the full `cargo check --workspace` (including ggen-lsp) both clean; `just pre-commit` (11 real gates: fmt-check, check, lint, test-lib 433/433, coherence-check, guard-process-intelligence-boundary, guard-cheat-scan 0 findings, guard-claims-schema, guard-pack-proofs, guard-generation-hash-pin, guard-pack-count) exit 0. `.github/workflows/ci.yml`'s `integration-tests` job promoted from advisory to a required dependency of `ci-status` in the same commit -- this SPOF is now genuinely, not just partially, closed: real integration-test failures now block merges, and the specific 10 that were silently red are gone." .

# Doc/implementation drift surfaced while closing CiIntegrationTestsNeverRun: `model.rs`'s
# own PROJ-407 comment states sh:sparql constraints are "rejected at shape load time" under
# CORE_ONLY, but the actual implementation (check_sparql_boundary/validate.rs:572) silently
# SKIPS evaluating them at validation time instead -- ShapesGraph::parse succeeds either way.
# Disclosed, not fixed: a real production shapes file (ontologies/shapes/process-conformance.
# shacl.ttl) uses sh:sparql and this pass found zero Rust call sites loading it by filename
# (grep across the whole workspace, excluding target/ and the third-party ontology_catalogue/
# mirror) -- so a load-time hard refusal MIGHT be safe, but that "zero consumers" finding is
# not strong enough evidence to change production load-time behavior within this pass's bounded
# scope (a silent, unproven consumer elsewhere would break on the exact shapes file the
# threat-model decision was written to still allow loading). Bounded accepted risk, matching
# this repo's own KnownDivergence disclosure pattern (packs/ggen-verify-pack/ontology.ttl):
# scope = the doc comment's phrasing overclaims what the code does, not that the security
# boundary itself is broken (sh:sparql constraints ARE inert either way -- CORE_ONLY's actual
# guarantee, "no SPARQL evaluation happens", holds); failure consequence = a shapes author who
# writes sh:sparql gets no load-time or validation-time signal that their constraint is a no-op;
# owner = this ledger entry; review trigger = before any change makes ShapesGraph::parse reject
# sh:sparql-bearing shapes, first confirm process-conformance.shacl.ttl (or any other sh:sparql
# shapes file) has zero real consumers, or update/remove it as part of the same change.
retrofit:ShaclSparqlBoundaryDocDrift a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "model.rs's PROJ-407 comment says sh:sparql is 'rejected at shape load time'; the real implementation silently skips it at validation time instead" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "DISCOVERED 2026-07-21/22 (retrofit/ggen-self-g4) while root-causing CiIntegrationTestsNeverRun's 3 sh:sparql-related test failures (shacl_validation.rs::test_sparql_ask_constraint/test_sparql_select_constraint + shacl_sparql_stress.rs::test_sparql_constraint_combined_with_ordinary_constraints, plus byte-identical duplicates in shacl_validation_extended.rs). `crates/praxis-graphlaw/src/shacl/model.rs`'s `SHACL_SPARQL_BOUNDARY` doc comment (PROJ-407 Step 2, a real v26.7.8 threat-model decision: smallest attack surface, deterministic non-network-dependent validation) states sh:sparql/sh:select/sh:ask constraints 'are rejected at shape load time.' The actual code (`shacl/sparql.rs::check_sparql_boundary`, called from `shacl/validate.rs:572`) does NOT reject at load time -- `ShapesGraph::parse` succeeds unconditionally for shapes containing sh:sparql; the boundary check instead runs at VALIDATION time and simply skips the `validate_sparql_constraint` call, so the constraint is silently inert rather than the shape being refused outright. The net security property (no SPARQL evaluation ever happens under CORE_ONLY) still holds either way -- this is a documentation/implementation MISMATCH about WHEN the boundary is enforced, not a bypass of the boundary itself. Bounded accepted risk (see the comment immediately above this individual for the full scope/consequence/owner/review-trigger record): fixing it to match the doc (reject at load time) is deferred because a real production shapes file, `ontologies/shapes/process-conformance.shacl.ttl`, genuinely uses sh:sparql (2 real constraint occurrences, confirmed by direct grep, not just a vocabulary mention), and this pass found zero Rust call sites loading it by filename anywhere in the workspace outside target/ and the third-party ontology_catalogue/ mirror -- not proof of zero consumers, just an absence of found ones, which this bounded pass judged insufficient evidence to safely flip load-time behavior on. Left correctly disclosed rather than silently fixed or silently ignored." .

retrofit:GraphLawValuesSilentZeroRows a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "praxis-graphlaw's SPARQL executor silently mishandled 9 construct classes -- FULL AUDIT + fail-closed refusal net, g15" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:SelfGenerationPath ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdateG15 "FULL AUDIT COMPLETED (retrofit/ggen-self-g15), upgrading the g13 single-construct repair to a systematic one: a 17-case probe battery against known data (committed as crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/sparql_unsupported_refusal.rs, both halves pinned) found the silent-unsupported class extends to 9 construct shapes -- silent ZERO rows: VALUES, ORDER BY, LIMIT/OFFSET, FILTER arithmetic, STRSTARTS/REGEX (any function but STR), EXISTS; silently WRONG rows: DISTINCT does not deduplicate, and worst, FILTER NOT EXISTS is IGNORED outright, returning the unfiltered set (fail-open). plan_query_or_refuse now walks the full spargebra algebra AND expression trees (find_unsupported_construct/find_unsupported_expression, exhaustive matches) refusing every probed-broken construct with a message naming it; probed-WORKING constructs (BGP, UNION, OPTIONAL+!BOUND, MINUS, plain-comparison FILTER, STR, GROUP BY+COUNT, subselects; REDUCED allowed -- non-dedup is spec-conformant for REDUCED) are pinned to still answer correctly so the net cannot over-block. Verified: full praxis-graphlaw suite A/B vs the g13 baseline -- the ONLY delta was this session's own g13 VALUES test (updated: gate 020 contains both VALUES and ORDER BY; naming the outermost is correct), the 20 pre-existing CI-invisible failures unchanged; all 5 hook-actuation suites + composed_packs_e2e + lint_validate_e2e + just test-lib green. Production gates remain unaffected (oxigraph mirror). Accepted: real VALUES/ORDER-BY/etc. implementations remain open work, but no unsupported construct can silently answer any more." ;
    retrofit:evidence "DISCOVERED and REPAIRED 2026-07-21 (retrofit/ggen-self-g13). Probed live: identical colliding data yields 2 rows for the same constraint expressed without VALUES and 0 rows with it -- no error, a silent false-pass for any violation-style SELECT. Blast-radius check BEFORE panic: production pack-gate evaluation is NOT affected -- GraphLawStore::query (crates/ggen-engine/src/graph.rs:850+) delegates all SPARQL to its oxigraph mirror, where VALUES works; the 39 packs/*/gates/*.rq files using VALUES evaluate correctly in real syncs. The defect was confined to praxis_graphlaw::TripleStore::query's own custom planner/executor (and thus kh: hook queries -- none of the committed hook packs use VALUES, checked). Repaired fail-closed rather than by implementing VALUES: plan_query_or_refuse now walks the parsed algebra (pattern_contains_values, exhaustive GraphPattern match) and returns a typed refusal naming VALUES and suggesting the UNION rewrite or the oxigraph mirror -- unsupported is now loud, never an empty answer. Proven by values_clause_is_refused_not_silent in dogfood_lifecycle_hook_actuation.rs; zero regressions confirmed via the full-suite A/B (identical pre-existing failure sets). Accepted: implementing real VALUES support remains open but the false-pass shape is gone." .

retrofit:NoBranchProtection a retrofit:SPOF ;
